comments.body:
@rhatdan It looks like podman-remote is passing the wrong URL query parameter to the API. From the looks of it the networks should be passed as reference={VALUE_FROM_CMD} but they are being passed as network={VALUE_FROM_CMD}. Because of this the command values aren't being decoded properly and no CNI Networks are being assigned to the pod.

See https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/60c90c3adda6f076092ea9f06618d94efb1b4708/pkg/api/handlers/libpod/play.go#L22-L30 for the backend API code. After looking at this file's history it looks like reference is the correct way to pass, but I defer to you. Perhaps reference is not correct and it should be network though?

In the meantime I'll try to debug the podman-remote tomorrow and give you a better idea of what is going on.
